    <!-- NOTA BENA                                 -->
    <!-- The DisplayAnchors JSON must be JSON!     -->
    <!-- JavaScript objects are not ok.            -->
    <!-- Use quotes around property names.         -->
    <script type="application/json" data-displayAnchors="true">
        {
            "displayAnchors": [
                {
                    "caseSensitive": true,
                    "startAnchor": "responsive_table_start",
                    "endAnchor": "responsive_table_end",
                    "removeEndAnchor": true,
                    "removeStartAnchor": true,
                    "displaySettings": {
                        "cellStyle": "text-align:left;border:1px solid rebeccapurple;margin:0px;padding:0px;",
                        "display": "responsive_table_single_column",
                        "tableStyle": "margin-bottom: 20px;width:100%;max-width:816px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;"
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    </script>

    <h1 style="margin-top:2em;">Introduction to Smart Sections Responsive HTML</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5em;">
    This Smart Sections HTML example file is used with the Docusign Smart Sections feature.<br/>
    </br/>
    When the file is viewed in a narrow window such as a mobile or tablet, tables 
    will be narrowed.

    Optionally, developers can add 
    <a href="https://developers.docusign.com/docs/esign-rest-api/reference/envelopes/envelopes/create/#schema__envelopedefinition_documents_htmldefinition_displayanchors"
        target="_blank">Display Anchors</a> via the 
    Envelopes:create API method to cause multi-column tables to be shown as single column 
    tables in narrow browsers. <br/><br/>
    
    The example tool enables developers to include the Display Anchors JSON in the HTML
    file itself.
    </p>

    <h1 style="margin-top:2em;">Other Supported Attributes</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5em;">Example:  &lt;ds-signature data-ds-recipient-id="1" <b>required="false" name="signature"</b>>&lt;/ds-signature> </p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5em;">
        name -- mapped to Docusign label property,<br/>
        title -- used for the Docusign tooltip,<br/>
        disabled,<br/>
        readonly -- mapped to Docusign locked property,<br/>
        pattern,<br/>
        maxlength,<br/>
        required,<br/>
        value,<br/>
        size,<br/>
        checked
    </p>

    <h1 style="margin-top:2em;">Supported Inline Styles</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5em;">Example:  &lt;input data-ds-type="text" data-ds-recipient-id="1" size="10" required="true" <br/>
        <b>style="color:DarkRed; font-size: 24px; font-family:Trebuchet; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic"</b><br/>
        name="Address" title="Address">&lt;/input>
    </p>
    <p  style="font-size: 1.5em;">
    color -- Only Docusign supported color names.<br/>
    font-size -- Use px. Eg "20px". The closest Docusign font size will be used.<br/>
    font-family -- Use a Docusign font family name.<br/>
    font-weight -- "bold" or "normal"<br/>
    font-style -- "italic" or "normal"
    </p>
